tent/uploads/2015/06/trj1.jpg\'); float: left; width: 100%; margin-top: 60px;\" align=\"center\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 80px 0;\">\r\n<h1 style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 30px !important; font-weight: bold !important; margin-top: 0;\">Make that dream Wedding Trousseau a reality</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #ffffff; margin-top: 3px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Trousseau by RJ is all about you! Marriage is the most important phase in the life of a woman and TRJ aims at making that occasion even more special through our exclusive trousseau consultation services.</h3>\r\n<span style=\"display: block; width: 100px; height: 30px; border: 2px solid #fff; line-height: 30px; color: #fff; font-weight: bold; cursor: pointer;\"><a href=\"http://192.185.26.69/~trjqa/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">CONTACT US</a></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Home Page Section 2','','inherit','open','open','','18-revision-v1','','','2015-06-23 05:02:45','2015-06-23 05:02:45','',18,'http://192.185.26.69/~trjqa/2015/06/23/18-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2015-06-23 10:14:10','2015-06-23 10:14:10','<h3><a href=\"http://192.185.26.69/~trjqa/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FAQs-banner.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-191\" src=\"http://192.185.26.69/~trjqa/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FAQs-banner.jpg\" alt=\"FAQs banner\" width=\"1340\" height=\"200\" /></a></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Q1 .What is Trousseau?</strong></h3>\r\nA Trousseau includes everything a girl needs during and after her wedding. It’s a compilation of items that her parents lovingly assemble and present to their daughter at the time of the wedding.\r\n<h3><strong>Q2. What does Trousseau typically include?</strong></h3>\r\nIt begins with the Bridal outfit but also includes jewellery, clothes for after the wedding, shawls, linen, Silverware, room furniture etc.\r\n<h3><strong>Q3. What is the importance of Trousseau in an Indian wedding?</strong></h3>\r\nIndian weddings are celebrated with a lot of pomp and splendor reflecting on the status of the bride\'s family. The bridal outfit for the bride and the family is an important part of the event, and it always leaves an impression.\r\n\r\nThe right Trousseau also helps the young bride and her husband begin their married life in comfort and luxury.\r\n<h3><strong>Q4. What is the usual way Trousseau shopping is done in families?</strong></h3>\r\nIn Indian families, the wedding is a collective event, and creating a Trousseau is no different. The family treats it like a mission where everyone wants to contribute. Often, they go about in large groups, choosing and buying after a common consensus.\r\n\r\nIn Indian families, the wedding is a collective event, and creating a Trousseau is no different. The family treats it like a mission where everyone wants to contribute. Often, they go about in large groups, choosing and buying after a common consensus.\r\n<h3><strong>Q5. What are the typical problems we end up facing?</strong></h3>\r\nThe size of the group often becomes a disadvantage, leading to compromises in order to make sure everybody gets a say. Family members with the best taste for fashion and décor are often overruled.\r\n<h3><strong>Q6. How can a professional help?</strong></h3>\r\nHiring a professional ensures that an innate sense of style and years of experience go into putting together a Trousseau of the highest quality. It also streamlines the entire process, right from the survey to the selection to the sourcing.\r\n<h5>       <strong>  1. Does it mean saving of time?</strong></h5>\r\nOf course! The consultant will zero in on the best merchants after surveying the market, and present to you   a   range within which a final choice can be made. Logistics are also taken care of.\r\n<h5>         <strong>2. Does it mean saving money/expense/cost?</strong></h5>\r\nYes! Years of experience in the market have taught our consultants where to source the highest quality material at the best price.\r\n<h5>         <strong>3. Does it mean organized, timely preparations?</strong></h5>\r\nAbsolutely. Having done the same many times, our consultants know where to go and what the potential bottlenecks are. Unencumbered by other responsibilities for the event, they follow a strict schedule while ensuring coordination between the different family members.\r\n<h5><strong>        4. Does it mean help in styling?</strong></h5>\r\nOf course! Our fashion experts take it upon themselves to ensure that your outfit complements your natural beauty so that you look your very best on your special day. Having a stylist also allows you to fully accessorise and customise your outfit, to the extent of hair accessories too if needed.\r\n<h5><strong>        5.</strong> <strong>Do we get guidance in the latest fashion trends?</strong></h5>\r\nYes, fashion styles keep changing and it’s difficult for an individual to keep up. However, it\'s important to know what the latest trends are. For instance, lengths of shirts, and types of fabric for women may vary from season to season, and sometimes, the combination may lead to asymmetry.\r\n<h5><strong>        6. Does Trousseau by RJ give us more options?</strong></h5>\r\nOur consultants give you access that would take you ages to research and discover. This includes relatively unknown designers and jewelers who produce classy material at reasonable prices.\r\n<h5><strong>        7. Can you help beyond Trousseau shopping?</strong></h5>\r\nAbsolutely, our experience in this field has brought us in contact with many reliable vendors such as dance coordinators, makeup artists, Mehndi wala , caterer, pandit etc. We’re happy to put you in touch with the right people, and help you where needed.\r\n\r\nAlso, we often help our clients in choosing gifts for the relatives and selecting outfits in all events for anybody who needs advise.\r\n<h5><strong>        8.</strong> <strong>Will you help us in packing and presenting the Trousseau.</strong></h5>\r\nAbsolutely. Good packing and presentation make all the difference. Can refer people.\r\n<h5><strong>        9. Does the Bridegroom\'s family require such services?</strong></h5>\r\nYes. Welcoming a girl from another family into their home is a delicate matter, and it\'s important they spend    time and effort on her things. The groom also needs special attention with his outfit, whether it is a coordinated turban and just, or accessories, and also for other wedding functions like chowki and cocktail that demand different sartorial styles.\r\n<h5><strong>        10. Does the consultant get handy for other family members?</strong></h5>\r\nYes, we assist everybody amongst the family and close friends.\r\n<h3><strong>Q7. Does it include Jewellery shopping?</strong></h3>\r\nYes. Jewellery comprises a large segment of Trousseau, and one needs to be very vigilant while buying it\r\n\r\nSome things to keep in mind while buying:-\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Allocate the amount</li>\r\n	<li>Divide it in the number of items</li>\r\n	<li>Prioritise- First decide the jewellery you’ll wear on your wedding, after matching with your outfit.</li>\r\n	<li>Diamond set, Polki, Gold are a must. You should also consider Jadau, Pearl and diamond, Rubies and Diamonds, Emerald, Blue sapphire, Yellow Sapphire and other precious stones</li>\r\n	<li>Try to have a varied collection</li>\r\n	<li>Avoid extremely heavy jewellery</li>\r\n	<li>Never buy too much jewellery in advance. You may keep raw gold but designs  vary from time to time.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe also help you if you want some multi-purpose jewellery items.\r\n<h3><strong>Q8. What happens if it\'s a destination wedding? Isn’t carrying jewellery is a big risk?</strong></h3>\r\nYes. However, we have a few vendors who manufacture jewellery that is such a good imitation that it is impossible to tell without a very close examination. It’s a safe option in such situations.\r\n<h3><strong>Q9. What about special requests from clients, like overseas wedding, overseas shippings etc.</strong></h3>\r\nWe are happy to make alternate arrangements to serve special requests\r\n<h3><strong>Q10. What will be the fee structure?</strong></h3>\r\nAfter a preliminary meeting in which the scope of the work is laid out, we settle on an amount acceptable to both parties. We usually have a retainer plus weekly payment schedule, however, we can always work out an alternate arrangement if convenient\r\n<h3><strong>Q11. How did you get into this field?</strong></h3>\r\nAs a child, I had a natural eye for elegance and detailing. I was also exposed to the world of diamonds at an early age, thanks to my dad, a jewellery manufacturer, who often designed diamonds for my mom with my help. My paternal family was also very fond of fashion.\r\n\r\nWhen I grew up, my opinions on the subject were always valued, and I often assisted family and friends in putting together their Trousseau and outfits. Later, I began designing and manufacturing jewellery. When business did well and requests to put together Trousseaus grew, I decided to pursue this full time.\r\n<h3><strong>Q12. Tell us about some of your experiences that convinced you to switch to this field.</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>One of my cousins living abroad was getting married in a couple of months. Time was a major constraint, so she asked for my help and was ultimately thrilled to have a well-coordinated and accessorized wardrobe.</li>\r\n	<li>I happened to accompany my sister to a jeweller in Delhi market of Delhi. She had ordered / selected some Italian gold sets for gifting, that were about to be packed before I found a flaw- the neck piece and the earrings were both in gold, but the engraving on them were different. The jeweller tried to convince us by saying that it was ‘mix and match’ style, to which my cousin would have agreed had it not been for me. It turned out that the assistant at the shop had interchanged another similar set and sold it to an unknown customer. This was their attempt to cover their losses</li>\r\n	<li>Once I was at Christie\'s in New York, waiting for a client with a friend. To help pass the time, we started observing random people and their clothes and accessories. After a while a lady who was sitting within earshot came up to me, complimenting me on my style sense. She was a buying agent / stylist for Gucci, and told me to get in touch with her if I ever got into a fashion business.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3><strong>Q13. What is the typical profile of your customers?</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>NRI\'s</li>\r\n	<li>People who are not so familiar with Delhi market.</li>\r\n	<li>People who are time constrained.</li>\r\n	<li>Perfectionists</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3><strong>Q14. Who can benefit from your services?</strong></h3>\r\nEverybody. We get clients from all walks lives and different income groups.\r\n<h3><strong>Q15. Do you keep any stock for sale to your clients?</strong></h3>\r\nNo. To avoid a conflict of interest, we sell our clients nothing from which we profit ourselves.\r\n<h3><strong>Q16. What do you as the future in this line of work?</strong></h3>\r\nWedding services is an industry that’s been growing every year. However, there are no services for Trousseau, which is a major part of every wedding, and one that can be quite challenging to accomplish. I certainly see more service providers entering this field, and with the money being spent on weddings, there’s certainly enough space in the market.\r\n<h3><strong>Q17. Is hiring a consultant expensive?</strong></h3>\r\nOur clients have found that the cost is more than offset by the reduction in time, and effort, along with the availability of the highest quality products at the best time\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','FAQ','','publish','open','open','','faq','','','2015-06-28 13:39:39','2015-06-28 13:39:39','',0,'http://192.185.26.69/~trjqa/?page_id=170',0,'page','',0),(171,1,'2015-06-23 10:14:10','2015-06-23 10:14:10','','FAQ','','inherit','open','open','','170-revision-v1','