om time to time.\r\n\r\nWe also help you if you want some multi-purpose jewellery items.\r\n<h2>Q8 . What happens if it\'s a destination wedding? Isn’t carrying jewellery is a big risk?</h2>\r\nYes. However, we have a few vendors who manufacture jewellery that is such a good imitation that it is impossible to tell without a very close examination. It’s a safe option in such situations.\r\n<h2>Q9 . What about special requests from clients, like overseas wedding, overseas shippings etc.</h2>\r\nWe are happy to make alternate arrangements to serve special requests\r\n<h2>Q10 . What will be the fee structure?</h2>\r\nAfter a preliminary meeting in which the scope of the work is laid out, we settle on an amount acceptable to both parties. We usually have a retainer plus weekly payment schedule, however, we can always work out an alternate arrangement if convenient\r\n<h2>Q11. How did you get into this field?</h2>\r\nAs a child, I had a natural eye for elegance and detailing. I was also exposed to the world of diamonds at an early age, thanks to my dad, a jewellery manufacturer, who often designed diamonds for my mom with my help. My paternal family was also very fond of fashion.\r\n\r\nWhen I grew up, my opinions on the subject were always valued, and I often assisted family and friends in putting together their Trousseau and outfits. Later, I began designing and manufacturing jewellery. When business did well and requests to put together Trousseaus grew, I decided to pursue this full time.\r\n<h2>Q12 . Tell us about some of your experiences that convinced you to switch to this field.</h2>\r\n<strong>1)</strong> One of my cousins living abroad was getting married in a couple of months. Time was a major constraint, so she asked for my help and was ultimately thrilled to have a well coordinated and accessorised wardrobe.\r\n\r\n<strong>2)</strong> I happened to accompany my sister to a jeweller in Delhi market of Delhi. She had ordered / selected some Italian gold sets for gifting, that were about to be packed before I found a flaw- the neck piece and the earrings were both in gold, but the engraving on them were different. The jeweller tried to convince us by saying that it was ‘mix and match’ style, to which my cousin would have agreed had it not been for me\r\n\r\nIt turned out that the assistant at the shop had interchanged another similar set and sold it to an unknown customer. This was their attempt to cover their losses\r\n\r\n<strong>3)</strong> Once I was at Christie\'s in New York, waiting for a client with a friend. To help pass the time, we started observing random people and their clothes and accessories,\r\n\r\nAfter a while a lady who was sitting within earshot came up to me, complimenting me on my style sense. She was a buying agent / stylist for Gucci, and told me to get in touch with her if I ever got into a fashion business.\r\n<h2>Q13 . What is the typical profile of your customers?</h2>\r\n<strong>a)</strong> NRI\'s\r\n\r\n<strong>b)</strong> People who are not so familiar with Delhi market.\r\n\r\n<strong>c)</strong> People who are time constrained.\r\n\r\n<strong>d)</strong> Perfectionists\r\n<h2>Q14<strong> .</strong> Who can benefit from your services?</h2>\r\nEverybody. We get clients from all walks lives and different income groups.\r\n<h2>Q15 . Do you keep any stock for sale to your clients?</h2>\r\nNo. To avoid a conflict of interest, we sell our clients nothing from which we profit ourselves.\r\n<h2>Q16 . What do you as the future in this line of work?</h2>\r\nWedding services is an industry that’s been growing every year. However, there are no services for Trousseau, which is a major part of every wedding, and one that can be quite challenging to accomplish. I certainly see more service providers entering this field, and with the money being spent on weddings, there’s certainly enough space in the market.\r\n<h2>Q17 . Is hiring a consultant expensive?</h2>\r\nOur clients have found that the cost is more